1
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:10,439
This slope sure is long.

2
00:01:13,439 --> 00:01:14,040
Chen Fan!

3
00:01:21,879 --> 00:01:22,879
No, no.

4
00:01:24,799 --> 00:01:25,560
I'm sorry.

5
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:26,680
I was just too excited.

6
00:01:26,879 --> 00:01:28,439
The letter... the Professor replied!

7
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:29,400
Look.

8
00:01:29,959 --> 00:01:30,799
That's great.

9
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:33,319
The Professor said my mom's case data is very typical.

10
00:01:33,519 --> 00:01:35,000
He's willing to provide the latest treatment plan.

11
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,319
Then my email wasn't in vain.

12
00:01:36,319 --> 00:01:37,480
I told you it would work.

13
00:01:39,239 --> 00:01:40,159
I used the rent money you gave me...

14
00:01:40,159 --> 00:01:41,439
...to buy a laptop.

15
00:01:42,159 --> 00:01:43,680
I've been refreshing my inbox every day.

16
00:01:44,359 --> 00:01:45,920
When I received this email just now...

17
00:01:46,519 --> 00:01:48,239
...it felt like I was dreaming.

18
00:01:48,959 --> 00:01:49,480
Oh, right.

19
00:01:50,079 --> 00:01:51,359
The Professor said he's free next Monday.

20
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,879
We can do a remote consultation.

21
00:01:53,359 --> 00:01:54,879
But we need to use something...

22
00:01:54,879 --> 00:01:56,719
...called a QQ video call.

23
00:01:57,439 --> 00:01:58,840
I'm not sure how to set that up.

24
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,480
That's simple.

25
00:01:59,879 --> 00:02:00,560
I'll be there too.

26
00:02:00,879 --> 00:02:02,400
I'll hook up a webcam for you...

27
00:02:02,519 --> 00:02:03,439
...and set up the network.

28
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,200
Thank you so much.

29
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:06,640
If it weren't for you...

30
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,120
...I really don't know...

31
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:10,719
Sorry about that.

32
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,479
I've received your gratitude.

33
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:13,520
But let's skip the hug.

34
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,960
I'm a model of male virtue.

35
00:02:15,719 --> 00:02:16,599
I'll carry this for you.

36
00:02:16,759 --> 00:02:17,479
I'm strong.

37
00:02:17,479 --> 00:02:18,000
No...

38
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,520
Um, I'll do it myself.

39
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,439
It's pretty heavy.

40
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,599
I'll do it myself.

41
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:27,159
Get closer to the microphone later.

42
00:02:27,199 --> 00:02:28,080
Otherwise the Professor won't hear clearly.

43
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:28,439
Okay.

44
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:30,479
Is the network stable enough?

45
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,120
Don't worry.

46
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,479
We're using the Education Network Line.

47
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:36,240
Brother Liang also prepared two modems.

48
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,599
We can switch if it lags.

49
00:02:38,639 --> 00:02:39,319
By the way, Chen Fan.

50
00:02:39,759 --> 00:02:41,719
I'll treat you after the consultation ends.

51
00:02:41,919 --> 00:02:43,680
My mom also wants to meet her benefactor.

52
00:02:44,919 --> 00:02:45,840
Let's not do that.

53
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:46,719
I usually...

54
00:02:48,199 --> 00:02:48,960
The Professor is online.

55
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:50,879
Hello.

56
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:52,520
Hello, nice to meet you, Ms. Wen.

57
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,159
Hello, Professor.

58
00:02:53,479 --> 00:02:55,120
So, are you the patient's daughter?

59
00:02:55,639 --> 00:02:56,319
Yes.

60
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:02,000
I wanted to ask what preparations we should make.

61
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:04,120
I have reviewed your mother's medical records.

62
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:05,000
Okay.

63
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:07,319
I need to confirm my schedule.

64
00:03:07,319 --> 00:03:08,479
Keep an eye on things here.

65
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:09,560
I'm going to the construction site.

66
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,479
Okay, leave it to me.

67
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:12,479
I understand.

68
00:03:13,879 --> 00:03:16,800
You need to stay calm and take good care of her.

69
00:03:19,879 --> 00:03:21,000
The sunshade is already set up.

70
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,599
The original water guns have been replaced with...

71
00:03:22,599 --> 00:03:23,479
...realistic laser guns.

72
00:03:23,719 --> 00:03:24,159
Oh, right.

73
00:03:24,479 --> 00:03:26,319
We've also triple-checked the safety measures.

74
00:03:27,159 --> 00:03:28,439
It's more efficient than I expected.

75
00:03:28,439 --> 00:03:29,199
Of course.

76
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,960
Later, we can put up...

77
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:31,719
...an Honor Wall at the entrance.

78
00:03:32,039 --> 00:03:34,280
We'll use gold, silver, and bronze tiers to display it.

79
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:34,800
What do you think?

80
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,759
That's a good idea.

81
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:39,960
Why don't we call it the Medal Club?

82
00:03:40,759 --> 00:03:41,719
Sounds good, Brother Fan.

83
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:42,759
Let's do that.

84
00:03:43,719 --> 00:03:45,439
After clearing the site next week...

85
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:46,879
...we can open for business.

86
00:03:48,479 --> 00:03:50,159
Speaking of the opening...

87
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,479
I feel like something is missing.

88
00:04:02,639 --> 00:04:03,319
Ms. Wen,

89
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,360
are you cooking for your mom again?

90
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,159
To thank you,

91
00:04:07,199 --> 00:04:08,080
I made this especially for you.

92
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,759
No, you don't have to be so polite.

93
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,599
You're making me feel embarrassed, really.

94
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:13,159
Please, don't stand on ceremony with me.

95
00:04:13,159 --> 00:04:13,840
Go have a seat.

96
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,319
It's too much trouble, Ms. Wen.

97
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,519
Yesterday's consultation was very successful.

98
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:22,199
Thanks to your networking,

99
00:04:22,399 --> 00:04:23,519
and technical support.

100
00:04:23,879 --> 00:04:26,480
So I wanted to cook this meal myself

101
00:04:26,879 --> 00:04:27,600
to show my appreciation.

102
00:04:28,319 --> 00:04:30,680
Also, I have good news to tell you.

103
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:31,759
What good news?

104
00:04:31,759 --> 00:04:32,439
The Professor said

105
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:35,000
there's a good chance my mom can be cured.

106
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,560
He invited us to go abroad

107
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,040
to join his experimental treatment program.

108
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:38,879
That's great.

109
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:40,399
I wish your mom a speedy recovery.

110
00:04:40,519 --> 00:04:42,600
And thank you for the meal you cooked today.

111
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,720
So when do you plan to go abroad?

112
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:51,839
And regarding the funds...

113
00:04:51,879 --> 00:04:53,399
The plan is for next week.

114
00:04:54,279 --> 00:04:55,120
As for the funds,

115
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:57,519
selling this house should be enough.

116
00:04:57,759 --> 00:04:59,480
As long as it cures my mom's illness,

117
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:00,759
that's more important than anything.

118
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:03,920
If you're really willing to sell,

119
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,439
could you sell it to me?

120
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,639
But out there,

121
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,959
there are plenty of newer and better houses.

122
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:10,759
Why does it have to be this one?

123
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,600
Ms. Wen,

124
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:16,399
do you believe in past and present lives?

125
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:17,959
I do.

126
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:22,240
But what does that have to do with this house?

127
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,879
I once had a dream.

128
00:05:27,759 --> 00:05:29,000
In that dream,

129
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,319
it was like I was in another world,

130
00:05:31,319 --> 00:05:32,680
living out most of a life.

131
00:05:33,639 --> 00:05:34,480
I had everything.

132
00:05:35,959 --> 00:05:37,040
Most importantly,

133
00:05:37,199 --> 00:05:39,000
I had the most understanding,

134
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,480
gentle, and beautiful girlfriend in the world.

135
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:45,800
Just as I was about to put the ring on her finger,

136
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,199
a car accident took her away.

137
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:52,879
Oh...

138
00:05:54,439 --> 00:05:55,360
In that dream,

139
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:57,800
we lived in a house just like this one.

140
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:02,600
Like the trees outside the window,

141
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:04,959
and the living room decor,

142
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,480
it was all the same.

143
00:06:06,879 --> 00:06:09,720
She loved making soup in that spot in the kitchen.

144
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,079
And she would always sit right here,

145
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,480
reading books or watching shows,

146
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:16,680
enjoying happy times.

147
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:21,120
Even more coincidentally, after I woke up,

148
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,439
I actually met her.

149
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:25,680
I think

150
00:06:26,279 --> 00:06:28,160
this might be a chance given by God.

151
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,079
So while for others, this house

152
00:06:31,439 --> 00:06:32,800
might be old and ordinary,

153
00:06:33,759 --> 00:06:34,839
for me,

154
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,600
it's a chance to make up for the regrets in my dream.

155
00:06:40,439 --> 00:06:41,279
I want her to live in

156
00:06:41,279 --> 00:06:42,959
the home I promised her in the dream.

157
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,600
I want to give this house to her as a gift.

158
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,040
To be cherished by you like that,

159
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:54,720
she must be very happy.

160
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:58,040
I agree to sell you the house.

161
00:06:58,879 --> 00:06:59,759
Really?

162
00:07:00,279 --> 00:07:01,199
Thank you so much.

163
00:07:01,199 --> 00:07:02,079
Let me toast to you.

164
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:03,800
Thank you.

165
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:10,040
By the way,

166
00:07:10,439 --> 00:07:11,040
in a couple of days,

167
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:13,199
I have an Airsoft Club opening up.

168
00:07:13,319 --> 00:07:15,199
If you have time, you can go check it out.

169
00:07:15,439 --> 00:07:17,199
Sure, I'll definitely be there to support you.

170
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:18,879
Um...

171
00:07:18,879 --> 00:07:21,920
we're currently missing a Brand Ambassador.

172
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,439
Are you interested?

173
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:24,879
Huh?

174
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,040
Right? It shouldn't be a problem.

175
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,600
We can also set up a sort of...

176
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,319
Membership system.

177
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:34,319
Like topping up cards.

178
00:07:34,319 --> 00:07:35,360
And then we can also give them

179
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,839
points on that card.

180
00:07:40,079 --> 00:07:40,720
Ms. Wen,

181
00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:41,600
this outfit of yours

182
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,040
is even more beautiful than in the game.

183
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:46,680
Is this really okay?

184
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:49,160
After all, I'm not a professional model.

185
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:49,959
It's excellent.

186
00:07:49,959 --> 00:07:50,800
Don't worry about that.

187
00:07:50,879 --> 00:07:52,399
We are all professional photographers.

188
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:53,600
The results definitely won't be bad.

189
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:54,759
Let's go, let's go.

190
00:07:54,759 --> 00:07:55,800
We'll head over first.

191
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:02,240
Wen Jie,

192
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:03,560
after the opening,

193
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,199
put a few more seats in the rest area.

194
00:08:05,319 --> 00:08:06,439
If people are queuing up,

195
00:08:06,439 --> 00:08:07,439
try to let them sit while waiting.

196
00:08:07,759 --> 00:08:08,319
Okay.

197
00:08:08,319 --> 00:08:10,439
And set up a big screen in the lobby

198
00:08:10,439 --> 00:08:12,040
to broadcast the battles inside the arena live.

199
00:08:12,279 --> 00:08:13,439
Great idea, Brother Fan.

200
00:08:13,439 --> 00:08:14,519
We'll go do that right now.

201
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:15,439
Go ahead.

202
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,040
Let's go.

203
00:08:18,319 --> 00:08:19,639
It's just about ready to open.

204
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:20,199
Yeah.

205
00:08:22,319 --> 00:08:25,040
After the opening, you'll be the Lady Boss.

206
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:29,600
Over there...

207
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,680
we originally planned to make a leisure area there.

208
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,279
But we changed it later.

209
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:34,440
That area actually turned out pretty well.

210
00:08:36,759 --> 00:08:37,600
It's the school.

211
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:40,399
Hello?

212
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,639
Is this student Chen Fan?

213
00:08:42,399 --> 00:08:44,039
I am Director Feng, the department head.

214
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,360
There is currently a report regarding misconduct.

215
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:48,639
You need to come to the department office immediately

216
00:08:48,639 --> 00:08:49,399
to verify the situation.

217
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:50,679
If you do not cooperate,

218
00:08:50,679 --> 00:08:52,840
it's an immediate demerit and expulsion per school rules.

219
00:08:53,159 --> 00:08:53,879
What do you mean?

220
00:09:00,879 --> 00:09:01,399
Chen Fan

221
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:03,120
You've got some nerve.

222
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:05,240
Daring to date a school staff member.

223
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:07,600
The school has repeatedly banned teacher-student romances.

224
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,960
And you just ignored it?

225
00:09:09,519 --> 00:09:11,159
No, Director, what are you talking about?

226
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:13,039
How could I be dating a staff member?

227
00:09:13,039 --> 00:09:15,320
There are photos of you hugging and cuddling.

228
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,679
And you still want to deny it?

229
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,000
No, Director.

230
00:09:18,039 --> 00:09:18,879
Can I take a look?

231
00:09:24,039 --> 00:09:26,039
This is way too fake.

232
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:26,639
Look.

233
00:09:26,919 --> 00:09:28,200
You can tell at a glance it's a composite.

234
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:30,039
The edges are so blurry they're fuzzy.

235
00:09:30,279 --> 00:09:31,000
This is obviously just...

236
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:31,440
Director.

237
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,000
Chen Fan.

238
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:33,879
Ms. Wen, look at this.

239
00:09:33,879 --> 00:09:34,799
What is this thing?

240
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:38,200
It's way too fake.

241
00:09:38,519 --> 00:09:40,039
We definitely didn't hug on the balcony.

242
00:09:40,159 --> 00:09:40,600
Exactly.

243
00:09:41,519 --> 00:09:42,000
Director.

244
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,639
Chen Fan is the buyer of my apartment.

245
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,639
And the former tenant.

246
00:09:44,879 --> 00:09:46,600
I actually came here to tell you about this.

247
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,399
So you're saying you aren't school staff?

248
00:09:53,519 --> 00:09:54,159
I am not.

249
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:56,000
But the apartment belongs to my mother.

250
00:09:56,039 --> 00:09:57,639
She is a retired teacher of this school.

251
00:09:57,799 --> 00:09:59,840
The agency has records of the relevant documents.

252
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:00,679
You can check them.

253
00:10:00,919 --> 00:10:01,639
Nothing is faked.

254
00:10:04,879 --> 00:10:07,519
Someone must have framed us with these photos.

255
00:10:07,759 --> 00:10:09,799
Who on earth took these photos?

256
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:11,639
I haven't offended anyone.

257
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:16,759
Ms. Wen, thank you so much for today.

258
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,639
Luckily, Xiao Pang reminded me.

259
00:10:19,039 --> 00:10:20,679
He said the school's staff apartments...

260
00:10:20,679 --> 00:10:22,519
...require reporting to the school for property transfer.

261
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,440
As for the photos...

262
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,440
...don't worry about them.

263
00:10:25,639 --> 00:10:26,519
What's fake can never be real.

264
00:10:26,639 --> 00:10:27,960
The school will investigate thoroughly.

265
00:10:28,879 --> 00:10:31,600
Just make sure your girlfriend doesn't misunderstand.

266
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,440
Um, I have something to do.

267
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,360
I'll get going now.

268
00:10:53,639 --> 00:10:54,159
Hello?

269
00:10:54,759 --> 00:10:55,480
Hello, Brother Liang.

270
00:10:55,639 --> 00:10:56,600
Have you seen Ruochu?

271
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:57,440
Is she still at the club?

272
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:59,440
Well... she went to the office to find you.

273
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:01,200
Not long after, she left with some photos...

274
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,440
...looking very upset.

275
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:03,960
Darn it.
